{"article_id":"Qm7EQX7LN6mVEmNz","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"A challenge to the way","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"a western New York State town board has had prayers read","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"before its public meetings","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"has made its way to the U.S. Supreme Court .","depth":4},{"id":4,"text":"The justices announced Monday morning","depth":4},{"id":5,"text":"that they will hear oral arguments in the case of Greece , N.Y. v. Galloway , Susan .","depth":4},{"id":6,"text":"The issue ,","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"as SCOTUSBlog writes ,","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"is whether a federal appeals court was right","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"when it ruled","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"that the town board 's practice violates the Constitution 's Establishment Clause ,","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"which reads :","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"`` Congress shall make no law","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"respecting an establishment of religion ,","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"or prohibiting the free exercise thereof ;","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"or abridging the freedom of speech , or of the press ; or the right of the people peaceably","depth":11},{"id":16,"text":"to assemble ,","depth":12},{"id":17,"text":"and to petition the government for a redress of grievances . ''","depth":12},{"id":18,"text":"As USA Today notes ,","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"the practice","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"of praying at public meetings","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"has been `` common in Congress and throughout the states for more than two centuries . ''","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"In the case of the Greece town board , though , Americans United for Separation of Church and State is arguing","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"that Christian prayers have been used so many times","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"that the officials are effectively endorsing that religion .","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"According to USA Today :","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"`` The group said","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"that two-thirds of the prayers","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"delivered between 1999 and June 2010","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"contained references to Jesus Christ , Your Son , the Holy Spirit or Jesus . ''","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"The lower court agreed ,","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"The Associated Press writes ,","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"ruling","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"that the town should have invited more people of other faiths '","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"to open its meetings .","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"`` Although the town did in theory allow anyone to volunteer ,","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"it 'neither publicly solicited volunteers to invocation","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"nor informed members of the general public","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"that volunteers would be considered or accepted , '","depth":11},{"id":39,"text":"the appeals court said .","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"`` The town also failed to make it clear","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"the prayer was intended to signify the solemnity of the proceedings ,","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"which","depth":13},{"id":43,"text":"the Supreme Court has said","depth":13},{"id":44,"text":"is not unconstitutional ,","depth":12},{"id":45,"text":"rather than 'to affiliate the town with any particular creed , '","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"it said . ''","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"On the other side of the issue is the conservative Family Research Council ,","depth":7},{"id":48,"text":"which has filed a brief in the case .","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"`` If the [ lower court 's ] decision is what the Establishment Clause requires ,","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"then Congress has been violating the Establishment Clause","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"since it was ratified in 1791 , ''","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"Kenneth Klukowski , a lawyer for the council , tells USA Today .","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"According to the council 's brief ,","depth":7},{"id":54,"text":"USA Today adds ,","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"97 % of the prayers","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"used to open House during the 112th Congress","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"were Christian .","depth":7},{"id":58,"text":"As for where the law stands ,","depth":5},{"id":59,"text":"the Los Angeles Times reminds readers","depth":7},{"id":60,"text":"that :","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"`` Thirty years ago , the court upheld a state legislature 's practice","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"of beginning its session with a non-denominational prayer .","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"The justices said","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"that 'to invoke Divine guidance on a public body","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"entrusted with making laws '","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"did not violate the 1st Amendment 's prohibition on an 'establishment of religion . ' `` But since then , several lower courts have said","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"that a city council or county board may violate the 1st Amendment","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"if its opening prayers favor one religion only . ''","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"The court will hear the case during its next term ,","depth":3},{"id":70,"text":"which begins in October .","depth":3},{"id":71,"text":"A decision would likely come around this time next year .","depth":2}],"relations":[{"parent":143,"left":140,"right":142,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":140,"left":77,"right":139,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":77,"left":75,"right":76,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":75,"left":74,"right":3,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":74,"left":0,"right":73,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":73,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":76,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":139,"left":117,"right":138,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":117,"left":88,"right":116,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":88